				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-552686#post-2026258</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-552686/scp-1535#post-2026258</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 05 May 2014 23:49:02 +0000</pubDate>
								<wikidot:authorUserId>1359534</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>I'm also left curious about origin. There's a historic and thematic disconnect between a 1946 glass mason jar and the Spanish Inquisition. My best supposition would be that it was a convenient container for the creator to use, and that they had a beef with inquisitions (probably something to do with having the ability to make anomolous objects).</p> </blockquote> <p>I think that's more of a question of how anomalous objects are created to begin with. I don't have a universal answer to that much better than <em>universal glitch</em> or <em>dimensional tearing</em>.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
